<br>
We should work up an estimate of the number of deaths they have caused by stopping nuclear progess over the last 30 years.<br>
<br>
If we had been building nuclear plants at the pace of 3 a year for the last 30 years, those 90 plants would have retired what percentage of coal plants?  <br>
<br>
Well, the 100 plants we have now generate 20 percent of our power, so another 90 would take that to 40 percent.<br>
<br>
Cutting coal's fraction from 58 to 38 percent, or reducing it by a third.<br>
<br>
So, one third of the people who die of black lung each year can be said to be the victims of Greenpeace in the USA.<br>
<br>
Is this a mean-spirited approach?  <br>
<br>
