flying out.  I should get myself into more trouble also by stating the fact that nothing can exceed the speed of light and that you will never observe anything exceeding the speed of light even if your moving away from it.  It blows common sense but if relativity is correct then lightspeed is the absolute speed limit both physically and &quot;observationally.&quot;  I.E. if two people moved in opposite directions at the speed of light they wouldn't observe the other ship moving away from them as travelling at twice the speed of light, but rather, just at the speed of light.  And the consensus seems to be that if things like tachyons exist (which can never slow down to the speed of light but always remain just above it) then they will travel backwards in time so the time dilations problems still exist.  Maybe there's some nifty way of getting around the time problem but I have no idea what it would be.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 12/10/02 7:32:42 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#6F6F6F>- </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace>NuclearSpace Message Board</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm15>Nuclear Waste</a> <font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href="http://www.nuclearspace.com">NuclearSpace Home Page</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
